article.description: Ronnie Boyce III scored 19 points, Tim Derksen added 16 and San Francisco beat Portland 87-76 on Thursday night.
article.headline: San Francisco has 6 in double figures, beats Portland 87-76
article.linkText: San Francisco has 6 in double figures, beats Portland 87-76
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Ronnie Boyce III scored 19 points, Tim Derksen added 16 and San Francisco beat Portland 87-76 on Thursday night. The Dons (11-9, 5-5 West Coast Conference) have won consecutive games since snapping a three-game skid. Portland (9-14, 3-7) has lost three straight and seven of its last eight games. Dont'e Reynolds chipped in 12 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for San Francisco, which had six in double-figure scoring. D'Marques Tyson scored a career-high 27 points and Alec Wintering had 24 to lead Portland. San Francisco had a 51-45 halftime lead, and opened the second half on a 12-4 spurt to stretch its lead to 63-49. Boyce and Reynolds scored four points apiece, and the Pilots missed 7 of 9 shots during the span. Tyson scored six straight points to pull the Pilots to 79-74 with two minutes left. Uche Ofoegbu converted a 3-point play, and the Dons made 5 of 6 free throws to seal it.
